			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I dont really see what the big deal is about a short tour manditory draft (18months or so). On one side I do agree with the 100% volunteer army but every day I am reminded of the constant stupidity of some people on military views, knowledge and issues. Christ, some people think we still fight in fucking trench wars, bomb/shoot anything that moves, etc, etc.
<br />

<br />
I have seen how the military can change a person for the better.
<br />

<br />
From day one these army core values are instilled in our everyday life. ie
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">LOYALTY</span>
<br />
Bear true faith and allegiance to the U.S. COnstitution, the Army, your unit and other soldiers.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">DUTY</span>
<br />
Fulfill your obligations
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">RESPECT</span>
<br />
Treat people as they should be treated
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">SELFLESS SERVICE</span>
<br />
Put the welfare of the nation, the army, and your subordinates before your own
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">HONOR</span>
<br />
Live up to all the Army values
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">INTEGRITY</span>
<br />
Do what is right, legally and morally
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">PERSONAL COURAGE</span>
<br />
Face fear, danger, or adversity(Physical or Moral).
<br />

<br />
Personaly i think this would cut the obesity count in the US dramatically. Provide free education and money for college. Give us dIscipline and self confidence in ourselves and in everyday life. I think it could also drop the crime rate along with the possibility of a successful terrorists attack, violent crime, etc. It would also drop the accident rate and general ignorance for firearms along with many others.
<br />

<br />
Some may think that "oh I am not a killer", ok there are so many non-combat MOS's to chose from. Out of shape..... ie lazy, whatever. I have college plans is a toatal BS statement......  when18 months, half could be spent in classes and provide college money,no intrest loans etc. Debt problems...... cant afford it.........I had a good friend of mine have 65K of personal loans erased for a 4year contract not to mention his choise of duty station and 10K signing bonus.
<br />

<br />
Everytime I hear draft and how angry it makes some people, I think that is fear talking. Freedom aint free, it is and has been paid for by centuries of hard work, determination and in some cases with blood.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=948719" target="_blank" class="postlink">Baron Morrick Gnomercy</a>
