				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There was a 10 month mandatory draft in France until a few years ago (that you could willingly extend up to 24 months).
<br />
 I was one of the last ones, since those born after 1-1-1979 were exempt, and I'm born on 12-16-1978  <img src="images/smiles/eusa_wall.gif" alt="Brick wall" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
I actually liked my experience, and thus am in favor for the draft. But then, it shall not become like in France, aka a draftee should spend his entire time in army having physical training, learning to fight and shoot, nothing else... 
<br />
In France it was just an excuse to have cheap laborers, as a draftee could be confined in a kitchen if he wasn't suited for training , taking a weapon once every 2 month. 
<br />
I had better luck than others because I was already physically shaped.
<br />

<br />
