				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">should have to send their children into war </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"> The only problem with this is you just jeopardized the lives of the rest of that unit and/or command. If the opposing forces find that the children of prominent figure heads are there, they will be targetted relentlessly. Granted their lives are already precariously placed by being in the region but it becomes more dangerous when you have all of the enemy focused on destroying you to send a political message.
<br />

<br />
I do not want anyone in my Marine Corps or my Armed Services that do not want to be there. There are enough problems of folks not really understanding or taking the time to try and educate themselves on exactly what being a Marine or Soldier, Sailor or Airman really means. What they are pledging. Then along comes Joe and Jane Civilian with a screwed up attitude because they are forced to join and serve where they do not want to be and they bring down overall morale. They also become complacent about the jobs they do and get someone who volunteered killed. Shiftless fecks like that are what is really killing the service now. Those that volunteer but get scared when the going gets tough. They then become the leaders that my Marines have to follow and deal with the bullshit. How can you sir, lead me and my Marines if you do not want to be there? How can you SSgt + lead troops into battle if you are standing way the fuck in the back.
<br />

<br />
Sure you can say put them in the positions that become vacant at home while those who volunteered go to fight however that wouldn't work because regardless of where you put someone, if they are angry about being there, they will still get folks killed. We have enough folks joining for the wrong reasons as it is. And by wrong reason, they join for college money knowing they may have to serve in a war or as the world's 911 force at any point in time yet when they are taken to task, they balk and cry.
<br />

<br />

