			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I was in the military for 7 years, and to compare it to slavery is about as crazy as anything I can think of.
<br />

<br />
There are many things in this country that you are 'forced' to do, and none of them compare in anyway to slavery.
<br />

<br />
My parents 'forced' me to go to school, and they in turn were 'forced' by the government to ensure I did.  That is hardly slavery.
<br />

<br />
I am 'forced' to pay taxes, and I hardly think that is slavery.
<br />

<br />
I am 'forced' to come into work for 40 hours a week.  I hardly think my company 'owns' me, and I certainly don't consider myself a slave.
<br />

<br />
I know of several countries in the world that have mandatory service, and I am reasonably sure noone would call them slave states.
<br />

<br />
What are you guys thinking?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
